      <section class="- topic/section ">
         <title class="- topic/title ">Adapter Board</title>
         <p class="- topic/p ">The adapter board is integrated
in the controller box. It adapts the interfaces of the SUVT controller
board to the mechanical build-up of the system.</p>
         <p class="- topic/p ">Functions of
the adapter board:<ul class="- topic/ul ">
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">All input/output signals of the controller box are routed via
the adapter board. All connectors of the controller box (except the
one to the power connection board) are directly mounted to the adapter
board.</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Decoupling of redundant supplies</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Four status LEDs</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Controller monitoring and selection of local master controller</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Galvanic isolation between ELV and SELV parts</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Measurement of bypass voltage via the measurement resistors
on the power connection board</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Driver circuits to use additional FPGA output signals</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Routing of signals from the power module connectors to the
controller board</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Charge current symmetry for the battery charger</p>
               </li>
            </ul>
         </p>
      </section>
